issues.fix:
Add a brief visual/audio cue before resetting, and optionally slow the rail near completion when cardsPlayed < 25 to give the game more breathing room. Minimal fix:

  if (rail.isComplete()) {
    // Brief pulse/flash to signal world-loop to player
    playSound('ambient_transition'); // reuse existing SFX
    rail.reset();
  }

Better fix: pause the rail when it nears completion (progress > 0.9) until cardsPlayed >= 20, then resume. This prevents silent invisible loops by synchronizing rail pacing with card progression.
